    "decisionConsequence": "Medium",
    "description": "FEA predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending. Validated by direct comparison to bench testing (N=11 constructs across two laboratories). Model influence MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence MEDIUM (pedicle screw fracture leads to revision surgery, not death).",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated",
    "intendedUse": "Demonstrate that the FEA modeling framework reproduces experimental compression-bending behavior of a non-cannulated pedicle screw construct within pre-established acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "name": "COU1: Non-cannulated construct compression-bending prediction",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "hasVerificationActivity": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/mesh-convergence-study-noncannulated",
    "type": "VerificationActivity",
    "name": "Mesh Convergence Study — Non-cannulated 7.5 mm Construct",
    "description": "A systematic mesh refinement study was conducted on the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model. Four mesh densities (coarse 1.5 mm, medium 0.8 mm, fine 0.4 mm, and ultra-fine 0.2 mm global element size) were evaluated. Construct stiffness and peak von Mises stress at the screw-rod junction were tracked across refinements. The Richardson extrapolation-based Grid Convergence Index (GCI) was computed for each QoI. Results demonstrated monotonic convergence with GCI below 2.1% for stiffness and below 3.4% for peak stress at the fine mesh density, confirming that the production mesh (0.4 mm) is within the asymptotic range. The study was executed in Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 under controlled solver settings documented in the verification plan VP-NONCANN-001.",
    "activityType": "MeshConvergenceStudy",
    "startedAtTime": "2025-08-10T08:00:00Z",
    "endedAtTime": "2025-08-14T17:00:00Z"
  },
