  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-noncannulated-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All three QoIs pass quantitative acceptance criteria (percent difference <10%, E/uval <1.96). Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted under a risk-informed decision given the medium model risk level, direct replication of the regulatory test scenario, and strong quantitative agreement across all QoIs. The mesh convergence study supporting the discretization error factor was completed and its results are discussed in the factor rationale and validation result narratives; the overall credibility evidence package is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level determination consistent with the COU risk classification.",
